<subSubSection pageId="125" pageNumber="126" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="125.[151,1437,897,2040]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1329,1356]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Description</emphasis>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[394,489,1330,1356]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">holotype</typeStatus>
is 
<quantity box="[520,573,1330,1357]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" unit="cm" value="4.0">4 cm</quantity>
high and 
<quantity box="[678,732,1329,1357]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" unit="cm" value="5.0">5 cm</quantity>
wide, the stalk is 
<quantity box="[923,997,1329,1357]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" unit="cm" value="1.5">1.5 cm</quantity>
long (
<figureCitation box="[1065,1158,1330,1356]" captionStart="FIGURE 97" captionStartId="118.[151,248,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@118.[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="118" captionText="FIGURE 97. Litophyton type specimens: a, L. amboinensis (Burchardt, 1898), holotype MZS NS 158; b-c, L. sanctuaryensis n. sp., b, holotype NTM C1387; c, paratype NTM C4383; d, L. swainensis n. sp., holotype NTM C1371; e-f, L. verrucosum n. sp., e, holotype NTM C4071; f, paratype NTM C3978." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765125" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765125/files/figure.png" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Fig. 97e</figureCitation>
). The polyps are up to 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" unit="mm" value="0.7">0.7 mm</quantity>
wide and high, grouped in conical catkins.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="125.[151,1437,897,2040]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,276,1402,1428]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Polyps</emphasis>
. With virtually no arrangement of sclerites as points (
<figureCitation box="[850,944,1401,1428]" captionStart="FIGURE 85" captionStartId="106.[151,248,1418,1443]" captionTargetBox="[158,1420,189,1384]" captionTargetId="figure@106.[151,1436,181,1393]" captionTargetPageId="106" captionText="FIGURE 85. Lateral views polyp armature of Litophyton species: a-b, L. folium n. sp., a, holotype NTM C4128, b, paratype NTM C10456; c, L. fusum n. sp., holotype NTM C4366; d; L. horseshoeensis, n. sp., holotype NTM C2256; e-f, L. sanctuaryensis n. sp., e, holotype NTM C1387; f, paratype NTM C4383; g. L. swainensis n. sp., holotype NTM C1371; h, L. verrucosum n. sp., holotype NTM C4071." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765101" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765101/files/figure.png" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Fig. 85h</figureCitation>
).Abaxially the polyp sclerites are unilaterally spinose spindles up to 
<quantity box="[391,487,1437,1465]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.50 mm</quantity>
long, with simple tubercles and spines (
<figureCitation box="[912,1018,1438,1464]" captionStart="FIGURE 104" captionStartId="126.[151,248,1607,1632]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1581]" captionTargetId="figure@126.[151,1435,181,1581]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURE 104. Litophyton verrucosum n. sp., holotype NTM C4071; a, abaxial point spindles; b, lateral point spindles; c, adaxial and tentacle sclerites; d, polyp stalk rods; e, supporting bundle spindles; f, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk. Scale at a also applies to e-f; scale at b also applies to c-d." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765139" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765139/files/figure.png" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Fig. 104a</figureCitation>
). Laterally they are up to 
<quantity box="[1287,1382,1438,1465]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.20 mm</quantity>
long (
<figureCitation box="[159,268,1474,1501]" captionStart="FIGURE 104" captionStartId="126.[151,248,1607,1632]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1581]" captionTargetId="figure@126.[151,1435,181,1581]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURE 104. Litophyton verrucosum n. sp., holotype NTM C4071; a, abaxial point spindles; b, lateral point spindles; c, adaxial and tentacle sclerites; d, polyp stalk rods; e, supporting bundle spindles; f, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk. Scale at a also applies to e-f; scale at b also applies to c-d." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765139" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765139/files/figure.png" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Fig. 104b</figureCitation>
). Adaxially there are rods and small curved scales, up to 
<quantity box="[879,976,1474,1501]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.10 mm</quantity>
long, similar to those of the tentacles (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 104" captionStartId="126.[151,248,1607,1632]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1581]" captionTargetId="figure@126.[151,1435,181,1581]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURE 104. Litophyton verrucosum n. sp., holotype NTM C4071; a, abaxial point spindles; b, lateral point spindles; c, adaxial and tentacle sclerites; d, polyp stalk rods; e, supporting bundle spindles; f, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk. Scale at a also applies to e-f; scale at b also applies to c-d." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765139" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765139/files/figure.png" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Fig. 104c</figureCitation>
). The polyp stalk has straight rods, up to 
<quantity box="[659,757,1510,1537]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.10 mm</quantity>
long (
<figureCitation box="[828,937,1510,1537]" captionStart="FIGURE 104" captionStartId="126.[151,248,1607,1632]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1581]" captionTargetId="figure@126.[151,1435,181,1581]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURE 104. Litophyton verrucosum n. sp., holotype NTM C4071; a, abaxial point spindles; b, lateral point spindles; c, adaxial and tentacle sclerites; d, polyp stalk rods; e, supporting bundle spindles; f, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk. Scale at a also applies to e-f; scale at b also applies to c-d." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765139" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765139/files/figure.png" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Fig. 104d</figureCitation>
). Supporting bundle not projecting or slightly so, composed of spindles, up to 
<quantity box="[500,597,1546,1573]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" unit="mm" value="0.8">0.80 mm</quantity>
long, with simple or complex tubercles and one spiny end (
<figureCitation box="[1247,1354,1546,1572]" captionStart="FIGURE 104" captionStartId="126.[151,248,1607,1632]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1581]" captionTargetId="figure@126.[151,1435,181,1581]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURE 104. Litophyton verrucosum n. sp., holotype NTM C4071; a, abaxial point spindles; b, lateral point spindles; c, adaxial and tentacle sclerites; d, polyp stalk rods; e, supporting bundle spindles; f, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk. Scale at a also applies to e-f; scale at b also applies to c-d." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765139" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765139/files/figure.png" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Fig. 104e</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="125.[151,1437,897,2040]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,474,1581,1608]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Surface layer top stalk.</emphasis>
Spindles, and unilaterally spinose spindles, all with simple and complex tubercles and tall complex spines (
<figureCitation box="[382,486,1618,1645]" captionStart="FIGURE 104" captionStartId="126.[151,248,1607,1632]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1581]" captionTargetId="figure@126.[151,1435,181,1581]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURE 104. Litophyton verrucosum n. sp., holotype NTM C4071; a, abaxial point spindles; b, lateral point spindles; c, adaxial and tentacle sclerites; d, polyp stalk rods; e, supporting bundle spindles; f, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk. Scale at a also applies to e-f; scale at b also applies to c-d." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765139" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765139/files/figure.png" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Fig. 104f</figureCitation>
). A few capstans and derivatives of capstans are also present (not depicted). Capstans 
<quantity box="[151,305,1653,1681]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" unit="mm" value="0.125" valueMax="0.15" valueMin="0.1">0.10-0.15 mm</quantity>
long; spindles up to about 
<quantity box="[599,696,1654,1681]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.60 mm</quantity>
long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="125.[151,1437,897,2040]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,474,1689,1716]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Surface layer base stalk</emphasis>
. Spindles, and unilaterally spinose spindles, all with complex tubercles and tall complex spines (
<figureCitation box="[233,339,1725,1752]" captionStart="FIGURE 105" captionStartId="127.[151,248,1496,1521]" captionTargetBox="[201,1386,181,1470]" captionTargetId="figure@127.[201,1386,181,1470]" captionTargetPageId="127" captionText="FIGURE 105. Litophyton verrucosum n. sp., holotype NTM C4071; a, sclerites of surface layer base of stalk; b-c, spindles of interior base of stalk; d, tuberculation of interior base stalk spindles. Scale at a also applies to b." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765141" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765141/files/figure.png" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Fig. 105a</figureCitation>
).A few capstans and derivatives of capstans are also present (not depicted). Capstans 
<quantity box="[1283,1436,1725,1753]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" unit="mm" value="0.175" valueMax="0.25" valueMin="0.1">0.10-0.25 mm</quantity>
long; spindles up to about 
<quantity box="[438,536,1762,1789]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" unit="mm" value="0.7">0.70 mm</quantity>
long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="125.[151,1437,897,2040]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,354,1797,1824]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Interior stalk</emphasis>
. Spindles, up to 
<quantity box="[540,604,1798,1825]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
long, with pointed ends (
<figureCitation box="[885,976,1797,1824]" captionStart="FIGURE 105" captionStartId="127.[151,248,1496,1521]" captionTargetBox="[201,1386,181,1470]" captionTargetId="figure@127.[201,1386,181,1470]" captionTargetPageId="127" captionText="FIGURE 105. Litophyton verrucosum n. sp., holotype NTM C4071; a, sclerites of surface layer base of stalk; b-c, spindles of interior base of stalk; d, tuberculation of interior base stalk spindles. Scale at a also applies to b." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765141" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765141/files/figure.png" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Fig. 105</figureCitation>
b-c) and simple and complex complex tubercles (
<figureCitation box="[243,349,1833,1860]" captionStart="FIGURE 105" captionStartId="127.[151,248,1496,1521]" captionTargetBox="[201,1386,181,1470]" captionTargetId="figure@127.[201,1386,181,1470]" captionTargetPageId="127" captionText="FIGURE 105. Litophyton verrucosum n. sp., holotype NTM C4071; a, sclerites of surface layer base of stalk; b-c, spindles of interior base of stalk; d, tuberculation of interior base stalk spindles. Scale at a also applies to b." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765141" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765141/files/figure.png" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Fig. 105d</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="125" pageNumber="126" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="125.[151,1437,897,2040]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,331,1870,1896]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Etymology.</emphasis>
The Latin 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Van" authorityYear="2020" box="[456,585,1871,1896]" class="Anthozoa" family="Nephtheidae" genus="Litophyton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="verrucosum">
<emphasis box="[456,585,1871,1896]" italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">verrucosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, warty, rough, rugged, refers to the internal stalk spindles with well-spaced coarse tubercles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1105,1941,1969]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="125.[151,1437,897,2040]" box="[199,1105,1941,1969]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,341,1941,1968]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Distribution</emphasis>
. Great Barrier Reef: Dip reef, Moore reef, Flinders Cay, Davies reef.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="126" lastPageNumber="127" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="125.[151,1437,897,2040]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,313,1978,2004]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Remarks.</emphasis>
The capstans and derivatives of capstans were present in small numbers and therefore not captured with the SEM images of the surface layer of the stalk.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765139" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3765139" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765139/files/figure.png" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" startId="126.[151,248,1607,1632]" targetBox="[151,1435,181,1581]" targetPageId="126">
<paragraph blockId="126.[151,1436,1607,1704]" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,292,1607,1632]" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">FIGURE 104</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Van, 2020" authorityName="Van" authorityYear="2020" box="[304,535,1607,1631]" class="Anthozoa" family="Nephtheidae" genus="Litophyton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="verrucosum" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[304,535,1607,1631]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">Litophyton verrucosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[541,602,1608,1632]" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[541,598,1608,1632]" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
,
</emphasis>
holotype NTM C4071; a, abaxial point spindles; b, lateral point spindles; c, adaxial and tentacle sclerites; d, polyp stalk rods; e, supporting bundle spindles; f, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk. Scale at a also applies to e-f; scale at b also applies to c-d.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="126.[151,1437,1750,1992]" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">
The species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Van, 2020" authorityName="Van" authorityYear="2020" box="[453,564,1750,1776]" class="Anthozoa" family="Nephtheidae" genus="Litophyton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="acutum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[453,468,1751,1776]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[483,564,1751,1776]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">acutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[571,656,1750,1776]" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
with regards to the surface stalk sclerites. However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Van" authorityYear="2020" box="[1240,1351,1750,1776]" class="Anthozoa" family="Nephtheidae" genus="Litophyton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="acutum">
<emphasis box="[1240,1255,1751,1776]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1270,1351,1751,1776]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">acutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the adaxial side of polyps without sclerites, different tentacular sclerites and spiny capstan derivatives in the surface of the stalk base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="126.[151,1437,1750,1992]" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">
NTM C3978 (
<figureCitation box="[356,457,1858,1884]" captionStart="FIGURE 97" captionStartId="118.[151,248,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@118.[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="118" captionText="FIGURE 97. Litophyton type specimens: a, L. amboinensis (Burchardt, 1898), holotype MZS NS 158; b-c, L. sanctuaryensis n. sp., b, holotype NTM C1387; c, paratype NTM C4383; d, L. swainensis n. sp., holotype NTM C1371; e-f, L. verrucosum n. sp., e, holotype NTM C4071; f, paratype NTM C3978." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765125" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765125/files/figure.png" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">Figs. 97f</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[469,511,1858,1885]" captionStart="FIGURE 106" captionStartId="128.[151,248,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[191,1397,181,1884]" captionTargetId="figure@128.[191,1397,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="128" captionText="FIGURE 106. Litophyton verrucosum n. sp., paratype NTM C3978; a, abaxial point spindles; b, lateral point spindles; c, adaxial and tentacle sclerites; d, polyp stalk rods; e, supporting bundle spindles; f, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk; g, sclerites of surface layer base of stalk; h-i, spindles of interior base of stalk; j, tuberculation of interior base stalk spindles. Scale at a also applies to e-h; scale at b also applies to c-d." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765143" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765143/files/figure.png" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">106</figureCitation>
) has unusual many polyp stalk rods resembling 
<taxonomicName authority="Van, 2020" authorityName="Van" authorityYear="2020" box="[1042,1198,1858,1884]" class="Anthozoa" family="Nephtheidae" genus="Litophyton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="brachiatum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1042,1057,1859,1884]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1072,1198,1858,1884]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">brachiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1205,1290,1858,1884]" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
but lacks the big interior stalk spindles with side branches of that species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="126.[151,1437,1750,1992]" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">
In group 
<collectionCode box="[296,315,1930,1956]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
also 
<taxonomicName authority="Van, 2020" authorityName="Van" authorityYear="2020" box="[371,471,1930,1956]" class="Anthozoa" family="Nephtheidae" genus="Litophyton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="folium" status="sp. nov">
<emphasis box="[371,387,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[399,471,1930,1956]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">folium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[476,554,1930,1956]" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" rank="species">sp. nov</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Van, 2020" authorityName="Van" authorityYear="2020" box="[605,799,1930,1956]" class="Anthozoa" family="Nephtheidae" genus="Litophyton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="sanctuaryensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[605,621,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[633,799,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">sanctuaryensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[805,888,1930,1956]" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
have sclerites with long spines. For the differences between the three species see 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Van" authorityYear="2020" box="[476,577,1966,1992]" class="Anthozoa" family="Nephtheidae" genus="Litophyton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="folium">
<emphasis box="[476,492,1967,1992]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[505,577,1966,1992]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">folium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
